  "prompt": "What are the best Allo easter eggs?",
  "response": "Allo, Google's smart messaging app, had several fun and quirky easter eggs that users enjoyed. While Allo is no longer available, here are some of the best easter eggs from when the app was popular:\n\n1. **Google Assistant Games**: Within Allo, you could engage Google Assistant in various games like trivia, emoji quizzes, and \u201cPac-Man\u201d. You simply had to type \u201c@google play a game\u201d to get started.\n\n2. **Emoji Reactions**: Allo allowed users to react to messages with emojis by long-pressing the message and choosing from a range of emojis. This feature often had playful, animated reactions.\n\n3. **Text Effects**: You could emphasize text in Allo by typing a message in uppercase and then tapping the \u201cup arrow\u201d to make the text appear larger, or the \u201cdown arrow\u201d for whisper mode.\n\n4. **Smart Reply**: This feature utilized machine learning to predict quick responses to messages, often with witty and contextually appropriate replies. It learned from the user\u2019s messaging habits to suggest personalized answers.\n\n5. **Doodles and Stickers**: Allo allowed users to draw on photos before sending them and had an extensive collection of stickers. Some of these stickers responded to certain keywords with animated actions.\n\n6. **Chat with Google Assistant**: You could hold a conversation with Google Assistant right within the app, asking for jokes, fun facts, riddles, and more.\n\n7. **Incognito Chat**: Allo offered an incognito chat mode that presented messages with a discrete notification and allowed you to set a timer for how long they would last before disappearing.\n\nRemember, while Allo was discontinued, many of these features are available in other Google services and apps, such as Google Messages and Google Assistant.",
